57.1	Scott_Weiland	Scott Weiland	Scott Weiland (born October 27, 1967) is an American musician, lyricist, and vocalist, most notable for his work with Grammy Award-winning rock band Stone Temple Pilots. Weiland is also known for his five-year career with supergroup Velvet Revolver as well as his own solo career. His onstage persona is known as being flamboyant and chaotic; he is also known for constantly changing his appearance and vocal style, as well as his use of a megaphone in concert for vocal effect. Despite his success, his career has been plagued with drug addiction, as well as several arrests. However, according to MTV News in 2010, Weiland has not used heroin since 2002.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/Scott_Weiland_%28Stone_Temple_Pilots%29_Open_Air_St._Gallen_%28rotated%29.jpg/220px-Scott_Weiland_%28Stone_Temple_Pilots%29_Open_Air_St._Gallen_%28rotated%29.jpg
